726468f-a.title: Queens: Dane Place - Fleet Street
726468f-a.text:
Dane elace (Telegraph poles thereon), east from about Fleet
Street. Shown at the left at the N.E. corner of Exeter and Dane
Place is the home of Wm. Boerum prior to 1873. At the right is
the Abraham Furman house, later known as the Miller house.
1922
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection

726466f-c.title: Queens: Dane Place - Fleet Street
726466f-c.text:
Dane Place, east from Fleet Street to Dartmouth Street,
showing at the left, at the N.E. corner of Exeter Street and
Dane Flace, the home of Richard SpragUe Jr. in 1852. It was
rebuilt about 186O and stood until Nov. 1933 when it was razed.
In 1873 it was a part of Mrs. Boerum's Estate. Views number 1
and 2 are taken looking westward.
1922
Views 283: Anril 1923
View 4: arch 1925.
